Let ${ a_n }_(n >= 1)$ be an infinite sequence with $a_n >= 0$ for all $n$. For
$n >= 1$, let $b_n$ denote the geometric mean of $a_1, ..., a_n$, that is $(a_1
... a_n)^(1/n)$.

Suppose $display(sum_(n=1)^(infinity) a_n)$ is convergent. Prove that
$display(sum_(n=1)^(infinity) b_n)$ is also convergent.
